The subject gives basic knowledge of periostitis, osteomyelitis and phlegmones, specific inflammations of jaws, cellulitis in the soft tissues in the maxillo-facial region. Aetiology, pathogenesis, differential diagnosis, treatment of these diseases is discussed.Students learn to diagnose these diseases. Practical work is at the Oral Surgery Department. Anaesthesia, tooth extraction instruments, methods and technique are taught. The clinical work performed by the student has been analyzed with the tutor, the student has received feedback and the work has been included in the student's e-portfolio.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to give the basic knowledge of stomatological diseases (odontogenic inflammations, specific inflammations of jaws in maxillo-facial region). Aetiology, pathogenesis, diagnosis and treatment is discussed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows medical deonthology 2) knows in detail anatomy in the maxillo-facial region and different teeth of upper and lower jaw 3) knows symptomatology in the maxillo-facial region diseases 4) knows methods of anaesthesia in upper and lower jaw and cranial base 5) knows possible complications of anaesthesia and complications after extraction. Is able to recognize the shock syndrome and is familiar with the treatment principles. 6) knows technique of extraction in lower and upper teeth 7) knows indications and general principles of atypical extractions 8) knows possible complications of extraction, complications after extraction, diagnostics, prophylaxis and treatment 9) knows different antibiotic groups and principles of treatment 10) is able to examine the patient and to compose the treatment plan 11) knows treatment of abscesses in oral cavity 12) is able to give advise to the patient about treatment possibilities after procedure in maxillo-facial region and write out a prescription 13) is able to remove teeth
